<subSubSection lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="36" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="33.[264,1323,398,1873]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,464,884,910]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Description.</emphasis>
Size 
<quantity box="[539,688,884,910]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1.2 mm</quantity>
. Usually dark-violet, extremities paler. Cuticle with fine but visible primary granulation. Ocelli 8+8, G and H smaller. PAO elliptical, not constricted, about twice as long as ocellus diameter or 0.8–1.3 of inner unguis length (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 87–92" captionStartId="34.[264,382,1488,1512]" captionTargetBox="[302,1272,694,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-267@34.[264,1322,686,1490]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 87–92. Scutisotoma schisti sp.n. 87, 88, anterior and posterior sides of furca; 89, dens, lateral; 90, PAO and ocelli; 91, tenaculum; 92, chaetotaxy of Abd.V." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071496/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 90</figureCitation>
). Maxillary outer lobe with 4 sublobal hairs, maxillary palp bifurcate. Labral formula 4/ 554. Labium with a complete set of papillae and guards. Proximal field with 3 chaetae, basomedian field with 4 chaetae. Ventral side of a head with 4–6+4–6 postlabial chaetae. Ant.1 with 2 basal microsensilla (bms, dorsal and ventral), and 2 ventral sensilla (s). Ant.2 with 3 bms and one laterodistal s, Ant.3 with one bms and 5 distal s (AO and one lateral s). Guards of AO clearly longer than inner pair of sensilla (Fig. 25). Males with some additional sensilla on Ant.2–3. Sensilla on Ant.4 hardly differentiated, the shape of the subapical organite either big and spherical (Taimyr), or small (southern Siberia) (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 93–98" captionStartId="35.[264,382,1393,1417]" captionTargetBox="[299,1298,739,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-233@35.[264,1322,726,1369]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 93–98. Scutisotoma schisti sp.n. 93, subapical microsensillum and organite on Ant.4 (Taimyr); 94, ditto (Tuva); 95, tip of leg 3 in male (Taimyr, B5, x: modified chaetae in male); 96, ditto (Tuva); 97, preanal chaetae (Taimyr); 98, ditto (Tuva)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071498/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs. 93, 94</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[264,1323,398,1873]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
All abdominal tergites clearly separated. Dorsal axial chaetom of Th.II–Abd.III as 9–10,6/5–6,5–6,5–6. Th.III with about 20 chaetae in p-row. Macrochaetae rather short, medial ones on Abd.V are 0.27–0.35 as long as tergite. Thorax without ventral axial chaetae. Sensillar formula 33/22224 (s) and 11/111 (ms). Medial sensillum on Abd.III set in posterior 1/3 of the tergite. On Abd.V the sensilla set in a line (
<figureCitation box="[1032,1121,1524,1550]" captionStart="FIGURES 87–92" captionStartId="34.[264,382,1488,1512]" captionTargetBox="[302,1272,694,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-267@34.[264,1322,686,1490]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 87–92. Scutisotoma schisti sp.n. 87, 88, anterior and posterior sides of furca; 89, dens, lateral; 90, PAO and ocelli; 91, tenaculum; 92, chaetotaxy of Abd.V." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071496/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 92</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[264,1323,398,1873]" lastBlockId="34.[264,1323,284,630]" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Unguis simple, without inner tooth (
<figureCitation box="[773,931,1564,1590]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–98" captionStartId="35.[264,382,1393,1417]" captionTargetBox="[299,1298,739,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-233@35.[264,1322,726,1369]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 93–98. Scutisotoma schisti sp.n. 93, subapical microsensillum and organite on Ant.4 (Taimyr); 94, ditto (Tuva); 95, tip of leg 3 in male (Taimyr, B5, x: modified chaetae in male); 96, ditto (Tuva); 97, preanal chaetae (Taimyr); 98, ditto (Tuva)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071498/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs. 95, 96</figureCitation>
). Ti.1–3 usually with 21-21-25 chaetae, B-row complete. Tibiotarsal tenent chaetae (1-2-2) truncate or slightly clavate, about as long as unguis (U 
<subScript attach="right" box="[575,583,1660,1674]" fontSize="6" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">3</subScript>
: t.ch. = 0.8–1.2: 1). Chaetae x and B 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1014,1022,1660,1674]" fontSize="6" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">5</subScript>
on Ti. 
<quantity box="[1099,1143,1644,1670]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
male short and chaeta-like (
<figureCitation box="[416,512,1687,1713]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–98" captionStartId="35.[264,382,1393,1417]" captionTargetBox="[299,1298,739,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-233@35.[264,1322,726,1369]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 93–98. Scutisotoma schisti sp.n. 93, subapical microsensillum and organite on Ant.4 (Taimyr); 94, ditto (Tuva); 95, tip of leg 3 in male (Taimyr, B5, x: modified chaetae in male); 96, ditto (Tuva); 97, preanal chaetae (Taimyr); 98, ditto (Tuva)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071498/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 95</figureCitation>
). Ventral tube with 4+4 latero-distal and 5–7 posterior chaetae. Tenaculum usually with 3+3 teeth and one chaeta, sometimes with an additional small tooth on one side (
<figureCitation box="[482,569,1767,1793]" captionStart="FIGURES 87–92" captionStartId="34.[264,382,1488,1512]" captionTargetBox="[302,1272,694,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-267@34.[264,1322,686,1490]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 87–92. Scutisotoma schisti sp.n. 87, 88, anterior and posterior sides of furca; 89, dens, lateral; 90, PAO and ocelli; 91, tenaculum; 92, chaetotaxy of Abd.V." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071496/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 91</figureCitation>
). Anterior furcal subcoxa with 12–18(22) chaetae, posterior one with 6–10. Anterior side of manubrium with a pair of distal chaetae, posterior side with 17–21+17–21 on the main part and 4+4 on the laterobasal lobes. Dens with 12–14(16) anterior chaetae, basal 1/4–1/3 without chaetae (
<figureCitation box="[895,1006,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURES 87–92" captionStartId="34.[264,382,1488,1512]" captionTargetBox="[302,1272,694,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-267@34.[264,1322,686,1490]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 87–92. Scutisotoma schisti sp.n. 87, 88, anterior and posterior sides of furca; 89, dens, lateral; 90, PAO and ocelli; 91, tenaculum; 92, chaetotaxy of Abd.V." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071496/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Figs. 87</figureCitation>
). Posterior side of dens crenulated, with 10–12(13) chaetae (5–6 basal, 2 (rarely 1 or 3) outer, 3 inner and 1 subapical chaeta near mucro (
<figureCitation box="[617,762,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 87–92" captionStartId="34.[264,382,1488,1512]" captionTargetBox="[302,1272,694,1467]" captionTargetId="figure-267@34.[264,1322,686,1490]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 87–92. Scutisotoma schisti sp.n. 87, 88, anterior and posterior sides of furca; 89, dens, lateral; 90, PAO and ocelli; 91, tenaculum; 92, chaetotaxy of Abd.V." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071496/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Figs. 88, 89</figureCitation>
). Mucro with 3 subequal teeth, lamellae hardly seen. Ratio of manubrium: dens: mucro = 5,2–7,4: 4,0–5,4: 1. Chaetotaxy of anal lobes as 
<figureCitation box="[296,437,444,470]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–98" captionStartId="35.[264,382,1393,1417]" captionTargetBox="[299,1298,739,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-233@35.[264,1322,726,1369]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 93–98. Scutisotoma schisti sp.n. 93, subapical microsensillum and organite on Ant.4 (Taimyr); 94, ditto (Tuva); 95, tip of leg 3 in male (Taimyr, B5, x: modified chaetae in male); 96, ditto (Tuva); 97, preanal chaetae (Taimyr); 98, ditto (Tuva)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071498/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Figs. 97, 98</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[264,1323,284,630]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,615,483,509]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Intraspecific variability.</emphasis>
Specimens from Taimyr and southern Siberia differ in the size of the subapical organite (
<figureCitation box="[621,764,524,550]" captionStart="FIGURES 93–98" captionStartId="35.[264,382,1393,1417]" captionTargetBox="[299,1298,739,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-233@35.[264,1322,726,1369]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 93–98. Scutisotoma schisti sp.n. 93, subapical microsensillum and organite on Ant.4 (Taimyr); 94, ditto (Tuva); 95, tip of leg 3 in male (Taimyr, B5, x: modified chaetae in male); 96, ditto (Tuva); 97, preanal chaetae (Taimyr); 98, ditto (Tuva)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071498/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Figs. 93, 94</figureCitation>
), in the differentiation of preanal chaetae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 93–98" captionStartId="35.[264,382,1393,1417]" captionTargetBox="[299,1298,739,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-233@35.[264,1322,726,1369]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 93–98. Scutisotoma schisti sp.n. 93, subapical microsensillum and organite on Ant.4 (Taimyr); 94, ditto (Tuva); 95, tip of leg 3 in male (Taimyr, B5, x: modified chaetae in male); 96, ditto (Tuva); 97, preanal chaetae (Taimyr); 98, ditto (Tuva)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071498" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071498/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Figs. 97, 98</figureCitation>
), and in some details of chaetotaxy of the posterior side of dens. We do not want to split the taxon at present, because of limited material.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071496" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5071496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071496/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" startId="34.[264,382,1488,1512]" targetBox="[302,1272,694,1467]" targetPageId="34">
<paragraph blockId="34.[264,1322,1488,1547]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,464,1488,1512]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">FIGURES 87–92.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg, 2006" authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[471,677,1489,1512]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schisti" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[471,677,1489,1512]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Scutisotoma schisti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[684,738,1488,1512]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[684,738,1488,1512]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
87, 88, anterior and posterior sides of furca; 89, dens, lateral; 90, PAO and ocelli; 91, tenaculum; 92, chaetotaxy of Abd.V.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="34.[264,1323,1592,1899]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,415,1592,1618]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Affinity.</emphasis>
Using the recent key of Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName authority="(Potapov 2001)" baseAuthorityName="Potapov" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[880,1211,1593,1619]" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Isotomidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Potapov, M." box="[1032,1203,1593,1619]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 603" refId="ref32250" refString="Potapov, M. (2001) Isotomidae. In: Dunger W. (Ed.), Synopses on Palearctic Collembola. Vol. 3, Abhandlungen und Berichte des Naturkundemuseums Gorlitz, 73 (2), 1 - 603." type="journal article" year="2001">Potapov 2001</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
the new species may key out as 
<taxonomicName authority="Stach" authorityName="Stach" box="[562,940,1633,1659]" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" genus="Proisotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="christianseni">
<emphasis box="[562,860,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Proisotoma christianseni</emphasis>
Stach
</taxonomicName>
, described from high mountain regions of western Asia (
<collectingCountry box="[569,678,1673,1699]" name="Lebanon" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
). About ten probable 
<typeStatus box="[943,993,1673,1699]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[1171,1322,1673,1698]" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" genus="Proisotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="christianseni">
<emphasis box="[1171,1322,1673,1698]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">christianseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[272,379,1713,1739]" name="Lebanon" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
, leg. Kowalski), deposited in the ISEA, 
<collectingCountry box="[850,931,1713,1739]" name="Poland" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Poland</collectingCountry>
have been studied.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[264,1323,1592,1899]" lastBlockId="35.[264,1323,284,670]" lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="36" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
This species belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bagnall" authorityYear="1949" box="[743,886,1753,1778]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[743,886,1753,1778]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Scutisotoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[1113,1188,1753,1778]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schisti">
<emphasis box="[1113,1188,1753,1778]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">schisti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having simple maxillary palp, 5 basomedian chaetae on labium, very dense chaetal cover of Abd.V, and some other characters. The simple maxillary palp and modified chaetom of Abd.V indicate an affinity of 
<taxonomicName box="[636,822,1873,1898]" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" genus="Proisotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="christianseni">
<emphasis box="[636,822,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S. christianseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
not to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[920,1030,1873,1898]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schisti">
<emphasis box="[920,1030,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S. schisti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" baseAuthorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[1128,1233,1873,1898]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oirota">
<emphasis box="[1128,1233,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S. oirota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" baseAuthorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" baseAuthorityYear="2006" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="36" order="Collembola" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fjellbergi">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="36" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S. fjellbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(for differences between these species see the key).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[264,1323,284,670]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
There is also one Nearctic species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mills" authorityName="Mills" box="[742,1093,324,350]" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" genus="Proisotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bayouensis">
<emphasis box="[742,1018,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Proisotoma bayouensis</emphasis>
Mills
</taxonomicName>
, which has a furca similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Potapov &amp; Babenko &amp; Fjellberg" authorityYear="2006" box="[489,600,364,389]" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Scutisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schisti">
<emphasis box="[489,600,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">S. schisti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(dens with 9–13 chaetae on anterior and posterior sides). Although the known differences of these species are rather minute or doubtful (4+4 tenacular teeth and a single tenent hair on each tibiotarsus in 
<taxonomicName box="[972,1245,444,469]" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" genus="Proisotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bayouensis">
<emphasis box="[972,1245,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Proisotoma bayouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), their different distributions indicate that they are separate species (
<taxonomicName box="[1009,1139,484,509]" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" genus="Proisotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bayouensis">
<emphasis box="[1009,1139,484,509]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">bayouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from subtropical 
<collectingRegion box="[466,587,524,550]" country="United States of America" name="Louisiana" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Louisiana</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="35.[264,1323,284,670]" box="[312,1205,563,590]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,465,563,589]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Distribution</emphasis>
. Scattered records from the high mountains in western Siberia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[264,1323,284,670]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,521,603,629]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Name derivation</emphasis>
. The name reflects peculiarities of the type-locality — stony, alpine sites with schisty substrate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
